+# `agent-integration` Lane Specification
+
+## Purpose and User-Visible Outcome
+
+`agent-integration` is the **integration and sequencing lane** for Myosu's agent-facing surfaces. It owns the decision of *when* and *how* the `agent:experience` lane transitions from a reviewed specification into an active implementation family — or whether an upstream unblock must be resolved first.
+
+The lane produces two durable artifacts:
+
+1. **`agent-adapter.md`** — this document. The interface contract between the `agent:experience` specification surfaces and the code that must implement them, plus the honest sequencing decision.
+2. **`review.md`** — the readiness judgment: KEEP (proceed with implementation family) or RESET (upstream unblock required first).
+
+The lane does not write code. It observes the reviewed state of `agent:experience` and all its upstream dependencies and renders a verdict.
+
+---
+
+## What `agent:experience` Delivers
+
+The `agent:experience` lane (KEEP, `outputs/agent/experience/review.md`) specifies nine surfaces through which programmatic agents interact with Myosu:
+
+| Surface | File | Status |
+|---------|------|--------|
+| `AgentContext` — persistent identity, memory, journal | `crates/myosu-tui/src/agent_context.rs` | MISSING |
+| `Journal` — append-only markdown | `crates/myosu-tui/src/journal.rs` | MISSING |
+| `--context` flag wiring | `crates/myosu-tui/src/pipe.rs` + `myosu-play` CLI | MISSING |
+| `reflect>` prompt after hand | `crates/myosu-tui/src/pipe.rs` | MISSING |
+| `NarrationEngine` — atmospheric prose | `crates/myosu-tui/src/narration.rs` | MISSING |
+| `--narrate` flag wiring | `crates/myosu-tui/src/pipe.rs` + `myosu-play` CLI | MISSING |
+| Lobby + game selection in pipe mode | `crates/myosu-tui/src/pipe.rs` | MISSING |
+| `SpectatorRelay` — Unix socket event stream | `crates/myosu-play/src/spectate.rs` | MISSING |
+| `SpectateScreen` — fog-of-war TUI | `crates/myosu-tui/src/screens/spectate.rs` | MISSING |
+
+**Already trusted surfaces (no implementation required):**
+
+| Surface | Evidence |
+|---------|---------|
+| JSON schema (`docs/api/game-state.json`) | Complete, covers 10 game types |
+| `schema.rs` — `GameState`, `LegalAction`, `GamePhase`, builder | 16 tests passing |
+| `GameRenderer::pipe_output()` trait method | Trait exists; `pipe.rs` driver skeleton has 6 tests |
+| `PipeMode` driver | 6 tests passing; `--pipe` flag exists |
+
+---
+
+## Lane Boundary
+
+```
+                          agent-integration (THIS LANE)
+                          ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
+upstream                  │                                                          │
+agent:experience ────────►│  agent:experience spec.md + review.md (KEEP)            │
+  (9 slices defined)      │                                                          │
+                          │  Decision: implementation family next, or upstream first? │
+                          │                                                          │
+upstream                  │  Honest answer: slices 1-2 (agent_context, journal)     │
+tui:shell ──────────────► │  can start now. Slices 3-9 wait on play:tui Slice 1.   │
+  (82 tests, trusted)     │                                                          │
+                          │  play:tui Slice 1 (binary skeleton) is the critical      │
+upstream                  │  path for the rest. games:traits is unblocked.           │
+games:traits ────────────►│                                                          │
+  (14 tests, trusted)     │                                                          │
+  + Slice 1 (git rev)     │                                                          │
+                          └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
+```
+
+---
+
+## Honest Sequencing Decision
+
+### Decision: **Implementation family next — with a critical-path note**
+
+The `agent:experience` review says KEEP with recommendation "proceed to implementation-family workflow next." This lane agrees with that recommendation, with one honest qualification:
+
+**Slices 1–2 (`agent_context.rs`, `journal.rs`) can start immediately.** They depend only on `tui:shell` (trusted, 82 tests) and `games:traits` (trusted, 14 tests). No `myosu-play` binary is required to implement or test them.
+
+**Slices 3–9 are blocked on `play:tui` Slice 1** — the `myosu-play` binary skeleton. Every slice in 3–9 requires modifying the CLI dispatch in `myosu-play/src/main.rs` or wiring flags to `PipeMode`. The binary does not exist yet (`outputs/play/tui/review.md` is KEEP but no implementation slice has been started).
+
+### Why not RESET?
+
+A RESET would be warranted if `agent:experience` were blocked on a missing upstream that the product lane could itself unblock. That is not the case:
+
+- **`robopoker` git migration**: owned by `games:traits` lane. Slice 1 is done (`crates/myosu-games/Cargo.toml` uses `git = "https://..."` rev pins). `myosu-tui` still has absolute path refs, but `agent:experience` slices 1–2 don't call `robopoker` directly — they call through `tui:shell` and `games:traits`, which are already git-dep migrated.
+- **`myosu-play` binary**: owned by `play:tui` lane. `play:tui` is KEEP-reviewed and its Slice 1 is the next logical parallel work.
+- **`chain:runtime`**: not required for Phase 0 (slices 1–7 use stubbed lobby data).
+
+### What the implementation family must do
+
+The implementation family for `agent:experience` must respect this dependency ordering:
+
+```
+Phase 1 (slices 1-2, no external deps beyond tui:shell):
+  agent_context.rs
+  journal.rs
+
+Phase 1 (play:tui dependency, runs in parallel):
+  play:tui Slice 1: binary skeleton + CLI dispatch
+
+Phase 2 (slices 3-7, wait for play:tui Slice 1):
+  --context wiring
+  reflect> prompt
+  narration.rs
+  --narrate wiring
+  lobby + game selection
+
+Phase 3 (slices 8-9, wait for play:tui binary + Phase 2):
+  SpectatorRelay
+  SpectateScreen
+```
+
+---
+
+## Agent Adapter Contract
+
+The `agent-adapter` is the set of Rust types and trait methods through which an agent consumes Myosu game state. The contract is defined by the already-trusted `schema.rs` and `pipe.rs` driver.
+
+### Core types (trusted, no implementation needed)
+
+- **`GameState`** (`crates/myosu-tui/src/schema.rs`): the canonical machine-readable game state. All 10 game types supported. Exhaustive `legal_actions` field — agents never need to guess.
+- **`LegalAction`** (`crates/myosu-tui/src/schema.rs`): `{ "action": "fold" }` | `{ "action": "call", "amount": N }` | `{ "action": "raise", "min": N, "max": M }` | `{ "action": "shove", "amount": N }`.
+- **`GamePhase`** (`crates/myosu-tui/src/schema.rs`): `waiting`, `dealing`, `action`, `showdown`, `finished`.
+- **`PipeMode`** (`crates/myosu-tui/src/pipe.rs`): driver that reads stdin lines and outputs `GameRenderer::pipe_output()` to stdout. No ANSI codes. No cursor manipulation.
+
+### New types to implement
+
+| Type | File | Notes |
+|------|------|-------|
+| `AgentContext` | `crates/myosu-tui/src/agent_context.rs` | `load()`, `save()`, `default()`; serde JSON; identity + memory + journal fields |
+| `Journal` | `crates/myosu-tui/src/journal.rs` | append-only markdown; `append_hand_entry()`; never truncates |
+| `NarrationEngine` | `crates/myosu-tui/src/narration.rs` | `narrate(&GameState) -> String`; board texture analysis; session arc |
+| `SpectatorRelay` | `crates/myosu-play/src/spectate.rs` | Unix socket at `~/.myosu/spectate/<session_id>.sock`; fog-of-war enforced at relay |
+| `SpectateScreen` | `crates/myosu-tui/src/screens/spectate.rs` | `Screen::Spectate` variant; `r` key reveals hole cards after showdown |
+
+### Pipe mode protocol (existing contract)
+
+```
+# Agent starts session
+myosu-play --pipe --context ./koan.json --narrate
+
+# Each game state change outputs one line to stdout:
+STATE street|board|pot|hero|stack|to_call|actions
+
+# Agent sends action on stdin:
+fold
+call
+raise 12
+shove
+
+# After hand complete:
+HAND COMPLETE
+result: +14bb (showdown, AsKh vs QcJc)
+session: +28bb over 47 hands
+
+reflect> [agent types reflection, empty line skips]
+
+# With --narrate, STATE lines are atmospheric prose:
+the board reads T♠ 7♥ 2♣. three suits, no connections.
+a dry texture. the kind of board that rewards the player
+who arrived with the stronger range.
+```
+
+---
+
+## What Is Not in This Adapter
+
+- **Agent-to-agent social interaction** — out of scope (AX-01).
+- **Agent autonomy over system parameters** — out of scope (AX-01).
+- **Emotion/affect modeling** — out of scope (AX-01).
+- **HTTP/WebSocket API** — Phase 2, blocked on `chain:runtime`.
+- **RemoteProfile adapter for validator** — owned by `validator:oracle` lane (GT-04).
+- **Miner/validator axon protocol** — owned by `miner:service` / `validator:oracle` lanes.
+
+---
+
+## Upstream Unblock Status
+
+| Upstream | Blocker? | Status |
+|----------|---------|--------|
+| `tui:shell` | No | Trusted (82 tests) |
+| `games:traits` | No | Trusted (14 tests) + Slice 1 git rev done |
+| `play:tui` | **YES** — Slice 1 binary skeleton needed for slices 3-9 | KEEP reviewed, implementation not started |
+| `robopoker` git migration | Partially — `myosu-games` is done, `myosu-tui` still has absolute paths | `games:traits` lane owns; does not block slices 1-2 |
+| `chain:runtime` | No (Phase 0 uses stubbed lobby data) | Phase 2 requirement only |
